The user comes with data that needs an annotation.
He interacts with the user interface only.
As the usage scenarios vary the server should provide
a user management that can be use optionally. Then it requires
not only the role of a user but also the role of an admin. An
admin is able to edit users and annotations. The admin should
be integrated into the ui if the user management is enabled. We prefer
an integrated solution to administration over an admin dashbboard.
The user interface allows to create annotations of arbitrary formats of data. It allows
the upload of the data which is stored in raw format. The file can be downloaded
later again if neccesary. If it is tabular data we want to allow users to reference columns
in the data for providing annotation content in certain situations. For example when providing
species names you can link a column that contains the information.
A link should be provided that allows
external databases to connect to the
the server, whatever is more performant)
